HEADWORD: Jabot
<hw>Jab"ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Originally, a kind of ruffle worn by men on the bosom
of the shirt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An arrangement of lace or tulle, looped
ornamentally, and worn by women on the front of the dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>jaboticaba</ent>⟦br⟧
